  (text "UNO Q HUB75 SHIELD — TOP-LEVEL BLOCK DIAGRAM\n\nSignal flow (IEEE 315: left to right, power top to bottom):\n\n  J4 (+5V_EXT) --> [POWER] --> +3V3 (LDO), +5V_EXT_HUB75 (direct)\n  J2/J3 (UNO Q headers) --> [UNO Q INTERFACE] --> SPI/I2C to ESP32-S3\n  [ESP32-S3] --> HUB75 GPIO --> [HUB75 DRIVER] --> J1 (IDC) --> Panel\n  [ESP32-S3] --> I2S --> [AUDIO CODEC] --> J6 (line out) / J7 (mic in)\n  [ESP32-S3] --> I2C --> [CONNECTIVITY] --> J8/J9 (Qwiic), J10-J14 (Grove)\n\nHierarchical sub-sheets:\n  sheets/power.kicad_sch           Power entry, AMS1117-3.3 LDO, AGND/DGND star, indicators\n  sheets/esp32s3.kicad_sch         ESP32-S3-MINI-1, decoupling, USB-C, EN/BOOT\n  sheets/hub75_driver.kicad_sch    74HCT245 x2 level shifters (3.3V->5V), HUB75 IDC\n  sheets/audio_codec.kicad_sch     ES8388 24-bit I2S codec, line-out header, mic-in header\n  sheets/uno_q_interface.kicad_sch J2 (SPI+CS_MCU), J3 (CS_MPU) UNO Q headers\n  sheets/connectivity.kicad_sch    Qwiic x2 (JST-SH 1.0mm), Grove x5 (2.0mm)\n\nApplicable standards:\n  IEEE 315 / ANSI Y32.2  Schematic drawing conventions\n  IPC-2221B              Generic PCB design standard\n  IPC-2152               Current-carrying capacity (replaces IPC-2221B Appendix B)\n  IPC-7351C              Land pattern (footprint) standards\n  IPC-A-600              Acceptability of printed boards"
    (at 20 185 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top)))
